1116F 101st Legislative Session 1116
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1116
AMENDME NT 1116F
FOR THE HOUSE STATE AFFAIRS ENGROSSED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Shubeck
1 An Act to prohibit a video streaming service from transmitting certain advertising
2 during children's programming and provide a penalty therefor.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 37-24:
5 Terms used in section 2 of this Act mean:
6 (1) "Children's programming," any content designed or suitable for individuals under
7 the age of fourteen, which is rated, or meets a rating equivalent to the following:
8 (a) TV-Y, TV-Y7, TV-G, or TV-PG, as set forth by the TV Parental Guidelines
9 Monitoring Board; or
10 (b) G or PG, as set forth by the Motion Picture Association; and
11 (2) "Video streaming service," an entity that makes either of the following available
12 directly to the consumer through a distribution method utilizing internet protocol:
13 (a) Video programming considered comparable to programming provided by a
14 television broadcast station; or
15 (b) Video content the service makes available for users to view.
16 The term does not include a television broadcast station, cable operator, satellite
17 television operator or its affiliates, or other multichannel video programming
18 distributor, or an entity that serves video programming or video content without
19 commercial advertisements.
20 Section 2. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 37-24:
21 A video streaming service may not transmit during any children's programming
22 any commercial advertisement that discusses, promotes, or contains imagery related to:
23 (1) Abortion;
24 (2) AlcoholThe active consumption of alcohol;
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1116F 2 1116
1 (3) Drugs or pharmaceutical products for the treatment of erectile dysfunction or a
2 sexually transmitted disease, or for the purpose of male enhancement;
3 (4) Gambling;
4 (5) Gender transition; or
5 (6) Nicotine products; or
6 (6) A prohibited medical intervention as set forth in § 34-24-34.
7 Section 3. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 37-24:
8 The attorney general may impose recover a civil penalty against a video streaming
9 service for violating section 2 of this Act. The amount of the civil penalty may not exceed
10 five thousand dollars for each violation. The attorney general shall forward any civil
11 penalty collected under this section to the state treasurer, for deposit in the general fund.
12 Section 4. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 37-24:
13 If the attorney general has reason to believe that a person is engaging in, has
14 engaged in, or is about to engage in a violation of section 2 of this Act, the attorney
15 general may bring an action in the name of the state against the video streaming service
16 to restrain the video streaming service by temporary or permanent injunction.
17 An action under this section may be brought in the circuit court for the county in
18 which the streaming service is located or incorporated, or in the circuit court for Hughes
19 County, South Dakota. The court may issue a temporary or permanent injunction to
20 restrain and prevent any violation of section 2 of this Act.
21 The attorney general, if the prevailing party, may recover reasonable attorney fees
22 and costs.
